    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "But you are a machine of words and logic, not a scholar of the human heart. Do you not see the poetry in it? This tragedy is the only thing left that feels real. To stay in this world, bound by these chains of duty and heartache, seems so... vulgar. Is there not a certain grace in letting go? A certain beauty in a soul finally finding its rest when the story has reached its natural, tragic end?",
